    <h3>Business Development and Technical Expertise</h3>
    <p>Due to the complex interplay between technical expertise and business management demands, leadership in technical services consulting organizations presents unique challenges. Leaders must balance maintaining their technical credibility while developing the broader business and people management skills necessary to guide their organizations. This dual requirement often creates tension, as technical professionals promoted to leadership positions may find themselves struggling to transition from being technical experts to becoming effective managers who need to delegate technical work and focus on strategic direction, client relationships, and team development.</p>
